      "faqs": [
        {
          "question": "How do I know if there are vacant positions in the municipality?",
          "answer": "Vacant positions are published in the Bulletin of Vacant Positions and posted in three conspicuous places within the agency. You may also inquire directly at the HRMO."
        },
        {
          "question": "Who can apply for a government job vacancy?",
          "answer": "Anyone who meets the qualifications for the vacant position may apply."
        },
        {
          "question": "What documents do I need to submit when applying?",
          "answer": "You need to submit an Application Letter, Personal Data Sheet (PDS) with a 2x2 photo, Transcript of Records or Diploma, Certificate of Eligibility, Training Certificates (if applicable), and Performance Rating (if applicable)."
        },
        {
          "question": "Is there a written examination and interview?",
          "answer": "Yes. Qualified applicants will be scheduled for a written examination (1 hour) and an interview conducted by the HRMO and the HRMPSB."
        },
        {
          "question": "How will I know if I passed the examination and interview?",
          "answer": "The HRMO will notify you regarding the result. Assessment of all applicants typically takes 2 days after the examination and interview."
        },
        {
          "question": "What happens after I am confirmed as a qualified applicant?",
          "answer": "You will be provided a checklist of requirements for appointment processing. Once all documents are submitted and the appointment papers are signed by the appointing authority, you will receive your appointment and take your Oath of Office."
        },
        {
          "question": "Is there a fee for applying for a government job vacancy?",
          "answer": "No, the entire application and appointment process is free of charge."
        },
        {
          "question": "What is the HRMPSB?",
          "answer": "The HRMPSB stands for Human Resource Merit Promotion and Selection Board. It is the body responsible for evaluating and screening applicants for government positions to ensure a merit-based selection process."
